ak Kyung Cha, and Cici Wu. Along theway, we learn what a racist joke has to do with the history of monochrome painting, if beauty has a partto play in social change, and whether whimsy should be taken seriously as a political affect. Carrolldraws attention to key connections between aesthetic pleasure and experimentation through theirshared capacity for world-building. Neither aesthetic pleasure nor experimental forms are liberatory inand of themselves; however, both can interrupt, defamiliarize, and rearrange our habits of aestheticjudgment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAestheticsxPsychological aspects2DLC. 0aAestheticsxPsychological aspects. 0aPleasurexPhilosophy2DLC. 0aPleasurexPhilosophy. 0aPower (Philosophy). 0aPowerxPhilosophy2DLC. 0aPowerxPhilosophy. 0aRace relations2DLC. 0aRace relations. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / African-American.2bisacsh  aBlack Literature.  aBooks about Black Literature.  aByron Kim.  aCici Wu.  aGlenn Ligon.  aIsaac Julien.  aJack Whitten.  aLiterary studies.  aNella Larsen.  aRace and aesthetics.  aTheresa Hak Kyung Cha.  aYoko Ono.  aZora Neale Hurston.  aaesthetic pleasure.  aexperimental literature.  aformal experimentalism.  ainterpretative practices.  aliterature and race.  aminoritarian aesthetics.  aperformance art.  aracial identity.  aracial politics and aesthetics.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z978311131826408iTitle is part of eBook pa